'''Steven Allan Spielberg''' [[Wikipedia:Order of the British Empire|KBE]] is an American [[Wikipedia:Film director|film director]] and [[Wikipedia:Film producer|producer]].

In 1980, Spielberg directed [[Wikipedia:Raiders of the Lost Ark|''Raiders of the Lost Ark'']] (1981), which Lucas executive produced. The pair went on to work together to produce and create the stories for [[Wikipedia:Indiana Jones and the Temple of Doom|''Indiana Jones and the Temple of Doom'']] (1984), [[Wikipedia:Indiana Jones and the Last Crusade|''Indiana Jones and the Last Crusade'']] (1989), and [[Wikipedia:Indiana Jones and the Kingdom of the Crystal Skull|''Indiana Jones and the Kingdom of the Crystal Skull'']] (2008).

==Biography==
Spielberg was indirectly involved with aspects of production of {{Film|IV}} (then titled simply ''Star Wars''). Spielberg introduced Lucas to [[John Williams]], who would go on to create the musical score for many of their films. Spielberg attended and enjoyed an early screening of the film. Lucas and Spielberg agreed to exchange shares in the profits of one another's films: Spielberg got a small percentage of the profits of ''Star Wars'', while Lucas would get a similar share of the profits of Spielberg's ''Close Encounters of the Third Kind.'' Spielberg continues to make money from the film.<ref>{{WebCite|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/george-lucas-star-wars-bet-made-steven-spielberg-millions-2014-3|text=How Steven Spielberg Made Millions Off 'Star Wars' After A 1977 Bet With George Lucas|author=Frank Pallotta|date=2014-03-26|work=[[Wikipedia:Business Insider|''Business Insider'']]|archivedate=20180131235102}}</ref>

During the animatic stage of of [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Revenge of the Sith'']], Lucas invited Spielberg to "play with" a bit of the [[Mustafar]] duel, and [[Yoda]]'s duel with the [[Darth Sidious|Emperor]], along with a couple of others, according to ''[[The Making of Star Wars Revenge of the Sith]]''. According to the [[Star Wars: The Complete Saga|''Star Wars'' Blu-ray]] release, Spielberg oversaw the animatic of an extended chase scene between [[Grievous]] and [[Obi-Wan Kenobi|Obi-Wan]] on [[Utapau]].

Being friends for years, Spielberg and Lucas have often traded references to each other's previous works in their films. For example, Indiana Jones is seen fleeing a nightclub named "Club Obi-Wan" in ''Indiana Jones and the Temple of Doom''. In Spielberg's film, ''E. T.: The Extra-Terrestrial'', Elliot showed some action figures, including [[Greedo]], [[Momaw Nadon|Hammerhead]], [[Ponda Baba|Walrusman]], [[Snivvian|Snaggle]][[Takeel|tooth]], [[Landonis Balthazar Calrissian|Lando Calrissian]], and [[Boba Fett]], to the alien of the film's title; later, E.T. met a child dressed as Yoda, whom he thinks is another alien, on the street during Halloween. In [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''The Phantom Menace'']], several members of [[Asogian|E.T.'s species]] were visible in one of the floating pods in the Senate room, and [[Senator]] [[Grebleips]] was named for Spielberg. Steven Spielberg made more films, like ''E.T. the Extra-Terrestrial'', ''Jurassic Park'', ''Jaws'', and ''The Adventures of Tintin''.

In January, 2001, Spielberg was made an honorary [[Wikipedia:Order of the British Empire|Knight of the Order of the British Empire]] by [[Wikipedia:Monarchy of the United Kingdom|Queen]] [[Wikipedia:Elizabeth II|Elizabeth II]] for his services to the [[Wikipedia:United Kingdom|United Kingdom's]] film industry.<ref name="KBE">{{WebCite|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2001/jan/30/news1|text=Spielberg receives KBE for services to British film|work=[[Wikipedia:The Guardian|''The Guardian'']]|archiveurl=https://archive.is/XllaG}}</ref>

